# BROWSER-core.md - LinkedIn Selectors & Browser Commands

## Browser Endpoints

```bash
# Open (first page only):
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/open -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"url":"URL"}' 2>&1
# Navigate (all subsequent pages):
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/navigate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"url":"URL"}' 2>&1
# Evaluate (run JavaScript):
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { ... }"}
ENDJSON
# Close:
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/close -H 'Content-Type: application/json' 2>&1
```

## Shadow DOM — Post/Poll/Repost Creation

LinkedIn renders the post creation modal inside `#interop-outlet` shadow DOM.
**ALL post creation UI (buttons, inputs, editors) are ONLY accessible via shadowRoot:**
```javascript
const host = document.querySelector('#interop-outlet');
const shadow = host.shadowRoot;
shadow.querySelector('button');  // finds modal buttons
```

See **BROWSER-post.md** for full post/poll/repost patterns.

## Selectors Reference

| Element | Selector |
|---------|----------|
| Notification container | `[data-finite-scroll-hotkey-item]` |
| Notification card | `.nt-card` (unread: `.nt-card--unread`) |
| Profile link | `a[href*="/in/"]` |
| Activity link | `a[href*="/feed/update/"]`, `a[href*="/pulse/"]`, `a[href*="/posts/"]`, `a[href*="/activity/"]` |
| Reaction count | `innerText.match(/(\d+)\s+reaction/)` on post container |
| Comment count | `innerText.match(/(\d+)\s+comment/)` on post container |
| Comment input | `div.tiptap.ProseMirror[role="textbox"]` — click `div[role="textbox"]` to activate |
| Submit comment | `button[data-view-name="comment-post"]` (appears after typing text) |
| Feed post container | `div[role="listitem"]` |
| Profile headline | `.text-body-medium` |
| Connection modal | `[role="dialog"]` |
| Note textarea | `textarea[name="message"]` or `textarea` |
| Inline editor (search/feed) | `div.tiptap.ProseMirror[role="textbox"]` or `[contenteditable="true"][role="textbox"]` |
| Inline comment toggle | `button[data-view-name="feed-comment-button"]` (opens/closes comment section) |
| Inline comment SUBMIT | `button[data-view-name="comment-post"]` |
| Article title | `textarea.article-editor-headline__textarea` (maxLength 150) |
| Article body editor | `[role="textbox"][aria-label="Article editor content"]` (ProseMirror, contenteditable) |
| Article "Next" btn | Find by `innerText === 'Next'` |
| Article "Publish" btn | Find by `innerText === 'Publish'` (in publish dialog) |
| Article share text | `.ql-editor[data-placeholder*="Tell your network"]` (Quill, contenteditable) |
| Article cover area | `.article-editor-cover-media` |

### Like Buttons (TWO TYPES)

**Type A (USE THESE):** `button[aria-label="Reaction button state: no reaction"]` — single click toggles. JS `.click()` works.
After click: `button[aria-label="Reaction button state: Like"]`

**Type B (avoid):** `button[aria-label="Open reactions menu"]` — opens dropdown, requires 2 clicks. Always filter for Type A.
